description:
&lt;p&gt;An excellent opportunity has arisen with London North West University Healthcare NHS Trust for an experienced, organised and enthusiastic Corporate Governance Officer to provide first class support service to the Trust&#39;s Corporate Office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This newly created post will support the Director of Corporate Affairs (DoCA) in promoting excellent standards of corporate governance. The post-holder will co-ordinate the administration and the decision-making processes and structure of the Trust Executive Management Group and its principal supporting groups. The post holder will be supporting the administration of specified Trust Board Committee meetings, forward planners and records and contribute to the production of the annual governance statement. This post will lead the Trust Wide policy management processes including the Standards of Business Conduct and write periodic reports on policy governance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have extensive minute-taking experience, including Board-level meetings, specialist knowledge and understanding of corporate governance, acquired through either experience or training, and be able to work in their own initiative as well as being a strong team player. You should have excellent attention to detail and strong organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will occasionally be required to travel between hospital sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePreetam MatharuJob titleHead of Executive OfficeEmail addresspreetam.matharu@nhs.netTelephone number020 8869 2005&lt;/p&gt;
